because we can get distracted

00:16:32.500 --> 00:16:35.059
by so many things that are going on.

00:16:35.059 --> 00:16:37.739
We can get distracted by all of the wickedness

00:16:37.739 --> 00:16:40.659
and the lawlessness and the erosion

00:16:40.659 --> 00:16:44.539
of what we would think has been a society

00:16:44.539 --> 00:16:47.299
that was built on Judeo-Christian values,

00:16:47.299 --> 00:16:48.339
et cetera, et cetera.

00:16:48.339 --> 00:16:50.619
And the reality is that we understand

00:16:50.619 --> 00:16:52.919
that evil men and seducers shall wax worse and worse.

00:16:52.919 --> 00:16:54.859
I mean, God told us that,

00:16:56.139 --> 00:16:58.500
but yet we must not be discouraged.

00:16:58.500 --> 00:17:00.299
We must not be distracted.

00:17:00.299 --> 00:17:02.299
We must get our focus upon the fact

00:17:03.099 --> 00:17:05.220
that we serve the God who is on his throne

00:17:05.220 --> 00:17:06.779
and who has all power.

00:17:07.739 --> 00:17:09.739
I notice in verse number four,

00:17:10.679 --> 00:17:11.519
the Bible says,

00:17:11.519 --> 00:17:12.940
his eyes behold,

00:17:12.940 --> 00:17:15.099
his eyelids try the children of men.

00:17:15.099 --> 00:17:16.419
Not only is he on his throne

00:17:16.419 --> 00:17:18.079
and not only does he have all power,

00:17:18.079 --> 00:17:20.739
but we find that our God knows all things.

00:17:20.739 --> 00:17:22.419
He knows all things.

00:17:22.419 --> 00:17:24.119
He knows about it.

00:17:24.119 --> 00:17:26.419
And that ought to cause us to rest.

00:17:26.419 --> 00:17:29.059
It ought to cause us to rejoice

00:17:29.059 --> 00:17:30.899
because we find that David says,

00:17:30.979 --> 00:17:32.579
and the Lord put I my trust.

00:17:32.579 --> 00:17:35.220
Now, again, as we mentioned in Psalm nine

00:17:35.220 --> 00:17:36.159
in verse number 10,

00:17:36.159 --> 00:17:37.000
the Bible says,

00:17:37.000 --> 00:17:38.819
and they that know thy name

00:17:38.819 --> 00:17:41.779
will put their trust in thee.

00:17:41.779 --> 00:17:45.139
For thou Lord has not forsaken them that seek thee.

00:17:45.139 --> 00:17:47.539
And David knew who God was.

00:17:47.539 --> 00:17:49.259
He knew, verse number four,

00:17:49.259 --> 00:17:51.039
that the Lord is in his holy temple,

00:17:51.039 --> 00:17:52.979
that the Lord's throne is in heaven.

00:17:52.979 --> 00:17:54.099
He was aware of that.

00:17:54.099 --> 00:17:55.779
And he declares in verse number one

00:17:55.779 --> 00:17:57.699
that I've put my trust in the Lord.

00:17:57.699 --> 00:17:59.739
And we find that he, David,

00:17:59.739 --> 00:18:03.379
is recognizing that though he does not have all power,

00:18:03.379 --> 00:18:05.599
though he does not know all things,

00:18:05.599 --> 00:18:08.000
that he serves the God who does.

00:18:09.019 --> 00:18:10.299
And this evening,

00:18:10.299 --> 00:18:12.940
we begin to think about these verses of scripture

00:18:12.940 --> 00:18:14.539
and we see where the Bible says

00:18:14.539 --> 00:18:16.259
that his eyes behold in his eyelids,

00:18:16.259 --> 00:18:18.099
try the children of men.

00:18:18.099 --> 00:18:22.019
We find that God was working on the behalf of David

00:18:22.019 --> 00:18:23.859
as we illustrated last week,

00:18:23.859 --> 00:18:26.699
looking at those examples in the book of 1 Samuel

00:18:26.699 --> 00:18:29.979
where God was defending and God was working.

00:18:29.979 --> 00:18:30.819
Why?

00:18:30.819 --> 00:18:33.080
Because God sees and God knows.

00:18:34.179 --> 00:18:37.200
There are times in which we go through life

00:18:37.200 --> 00:18:39.380
and we might have this perspective

00:18:39.380 --> 00:18:41.839
no one really understands.

00:18:43.019 --> 00:18:45.700
But we fail to recognize that our God

00:18:45.700 --> 00:18:49.059
has a deep, intimate understanding

00:18:49.059 --> 00:18:50.700
of everything that we face

00:18:50.700 --> 00:18:52.659
and everything that we're dealing with.

00:18:53.539 --> 00:18:55.659
And our God will give us the strength

00:18:55.659 --> 00:18:57.739
and the grace that we need.

00:18:57.739 --> 00:19:00.539
And so really when we begin to look at this question

00:19:00.539 --> 00:19:03.179
that is asked at the end of verse number three,

00:19:03.179 --> 00:19:06.539
when we look at it from a human perspective,

00:19:06.539 --> 00:19:08.219
what can the righteous do?

00:19:08.219 --> 00:19:10.859
We can come to that place of saying nothing.

00:19:10.859 --> 00:19:13.000
I mean, it's just useless, it's hopeless.

00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:15.859
I mean, there's nothing that's gonna change this.

00:19:15.859 --> 00:19:19.099
It's going so quickly in the wrong direction

00:19:19.099 --> 00:19:20.539
and it's just pointless.

00:19:20.539 --> 00:19:22.580
And from a human perspective,

00:19:22.580 --> 00:19:27.500
we'll just kind of get out of the game, so to speak.

00:19:27.500 --> 00:19:29.380
Get on the sidelines, throw up our hands

00:19:29.380 --> 00:19:31.080
and say, what's the use?

00:19:32.440 --> 00:19:35.940
But when we have a proper perspective,

00:19:35.940 --> 00:19:38.059
when we see God in His rightful place,

00:19:38.059 --> 00:19:40.080
when we understand that He's on His throne,

00:19:40.080 --> 00:19:42.659
that He has all power, that He knows all things

00:19:42.659 --> 00:19:43.739
and He sees all things,

00:19:43.739 --> 00:19:46.820
then we understand that what the righteous can do

00:19:46.820 --> 00:19:49.700
is everything that God has commanded us to do.

00:19:49.700 --> 00:19:51.419
That we continue to go forth,

00:19:51.419 --> 00:19:54.700
we continue to do what God has called us to do,

00:19:54.700 --> 00:19:56.219
what He's commissioned us to do.

00:19:56.219 --> 00:19:57.059
Why?

00:19:57.059 --> 00:19:59.659
Because God will work and God will bless.

00:19:59.659 --> 00:20:04.019
And God sees and God works.

00:20:04.019 --> 00:20:09.539
And it's not based on my power or on your power, it's based on His power.

00:20:09.539 --> 00:20:14.379
He said this, but you shall receive power after that the Holy Ghost has come upon you.

00:20:14.379 --> 00:20:19.859
That means that I don't have the power, it's the Holy Spirit of God who empowers me.

00:20:19.859 --> 00:20:20.959
Amen?

00:20:20.959 --> 00:20:24.959
My words are not powerful and neither are yours.

00:20:24.959 --> 00:20:28.179
But God's words are powerful, are they not?

00:20:28.179 --> 00:20:32.999
It's quick and sharp, it's powerful, it's a living book.

00:20:32.999 --> 00:20:40.599
We find that as we go forth in the path in which God has laid before us to do the work

00:20:40.599 --> 00:20:45.319
that He has called us to do, we do not get our eyes on the fact that the foundations

00:20:45.319 --> 00:20:48.919
are eroding and look at the societal collapse.

00:20:48.919 --> 00:20:54.319
No, we keep our eyes on Jesus, the author and finisher of our faith, and we understand

00:20:54.319 --> 00:20:58.859
that He is in control and He rules and He reigns and we just continue doing what He's

00:20:58.859 --> 00:21:01.459
called us to do.

00:21:01.459 --> 00:21:04.419
And then we leave all the results for God.

00:21:04.419 --> 00:21:10.819
It's a wonderful thing to be able to leave it in the hands of God, that God can accomplish

00:21:10.819 --> 00:21:17.059
and God can do what we cannot do, what we're incapable of doing.

00:21:17.059 --> 00:21:21.559
Have you ever tried to use a witty argument with someone to try to convince them of some

00:21:21.559 --> 00:21:22.559
Bible truth?

00:21:22.779 --> 00:21:26.899
I mean, you try to come up with the best illustrations and analogies and all this sort of thing and

00:21:26.899 --> 00:21:27.979
you know what you find out?

00:21:27.979 --> 00:21:30.579
Your words are not powerful.

00:21:30.579 --> 00:21:33.539
It's God's words that are powerful.

00:21:33.539 --> 00:21:35.619
We just give the truth.

00:21:35.619 --> 00:21:38.099
We just continue to trust God.

00:21:38.099 --> 00:21:43.059
The reality is that there are times in which as David is, and again as you study the book

00:21:43.059 --> 00:21:50.139
of Psalms, as you study and read through the Psalms, you find so often the transparency

00:21:50.159 --> 00:21:54.799
of the Psalmist, that David is pouring his heart out before the Lord.

00:21:54.799 --> 00:21:59.079
He's not the author of all the Psalms obviously, but in the ones that are the Davidic Psalms,

00:21:59.079 --> 00:22:02.999
we find that there's such transparency.

00:22:02.999 --> 00:22:06.879
And for us this evening, it helps us.

00:22:06.879 --> 00:22:08.079
Why?

00:22:08.079 --> 00:22:12.159
Because there are times that we face circumstances that we feel the same way.

00:22:12.159 --> 00:22:13.199
What's the point?

00:22:13.199 --> 00:22:14.839
No one wants to hear.

00:22:14.839 --> 00:22:18.159
No one cares.

00:22:18.159 --> 00:22:22.299
Those thoughts will go in your head, and it will discourage you, and it will defeat

00:22:22.299 --> 00:22:23.299
you.

00:22:23.299 --> 00:22:29.339
But no, we get our eyes on Jesus and say, He's on His throne.

00:22:29.339 --> 00:22:30.619
He's got all power.

00:22:30.619 --> 00:22:31.619
He knows all things.

00:22:31.619 --> 00:22:38.979
And by the way, He didn't tell me to go and to give the truth and to preach the gospel.

00:22:38.979 --> 00:22:41.939
He didn't tell me to do all of that so that I could have results.

00:22:41.939 --> 00:22:47.739
He told me to do it as a matter of obedience, as a matter of obedience.

00:22:48.319 --> 00:22:49.719
And as I obey Him, guess what He does?

00:22:49.719 --> 00:22:51.039
He blesses obedience.

00:22:51.039 --> 00:22:54.399
That principle is found throughout the Scriptures.

00:22:54.399 --> 00:23:00.039
And so we begin to look at this passage and begin to find in the life of David that there's

00:23:00.039 --> 00:23:06.799
so many relevant aspects to what he was dealing with and what he was facing.

00:23:06.799 --> 00:23:10.199
And yet he was not going to be shaken by it.

00:23:10.199 --> 00:23:11.199
Why?

00:23:11.199 --> 00:23:17.519
Because of the first statement in the Psalm, in the Lord put I my trust.

00:23:18.299 --> 00:23:24.779
And it's so vital for us this evening to have had that declared position that I've put my

00:23:24.779 --> 00:23:26.579
trust in the Lord.

00:23:26.579 --> 00:23:27.979
But look at all these things that are going on.

00:23:27.979 --> 00:23:29.659
Yeah, but I'm trusting God.

00:23:29.659 --> 00:23:32.339
I'm not trusting the government.

00:23:32.339 --> 00:23:37.579
I'm not trusting the, you fill in the blank, whatever it is that could be trusted.

00:23:37.579 --> 00:23:42.059
They will fail you, but God never will fail us.

00:23:42.059 --> 00:23:48.639
And it's a simple shift of perspective from the foundations being destroyed to the Lord

00:23:48.639 --> 00:23:55.239
being in His holy temple and the Lord's throne is in heaven and how we need to get our eyes

00:23:55.239 --> 00:23:56.239
on Jesus.

00:23:56.239 --> 00:23:59.879
Remember what the Psalmist said in Psalm 121, and I'll finish with this, I will lift up

00:23:59.879 --> 00:24:04.119
mine eyes unto the hills from whence cometh my help.

00:24:04.119 --> 00:24:06.799
That's an action, is it not?

00:24:06.799 --> 00:24:07.799
It's an action.

00:24:07.799 --> 00:24:10.199
I will lift up mine eyes.

00:24:10.499 --> 00:24:13.339
Something that we have to do, something that we have to purpose to do.

00:24:13.339 --> 00:24:14.339
Why?

00:24:14.339 --> 00:24:16.179
Because you know what your tendency is and my tendency is?

00:24:16.179 --> 00:24:20.899
It's to look at all of the temporal things because it's what's right in front of us.

00:24:20.899 --> 00:24:21.899
It's what we're seeing.

00:24:21.899 --> 00:24:22.899
It's what we're experiencing.

00:24:22.899 --> 00:24:24.599
It's what we're dealing with every day.

00:24:24.599 --> 00:24:27.579
And the Psalmist says, I will lift up mine eyes into the hills from whence cometh my

00:24:27.579 --> 00:24:28.579
help.

00:24:28.579 --> 00:24:32.939
My help cometh from the Lord, which made heaven and earth.

00:24:32.939 --> 00:24:37.339
And what a joy to know that our God is the creator and He is our helper.

00:24:37.339 --> 00:24:38.339
Let's pray together.

00:24:38.339 --> 00:24:39.339
Father, we love you.

00:24:39.479 --> 00:24:40.479
Thank you for accepting us.

00:24:40.479 --> 00:24:42.879
Thank you for the opportunity that you've given us to gather.

00:24:42.879 --> 00:24:48.679
And Lord, we're excited about the opportunity to just serve you in these days and to see

00:24:48.679 --> 00:24:51.159
what you could accomplish through us.

00:24:51.159 --> 00:24:54.639
I pray, God, that you would help us to be yielded and surrendered.

00:24:54.639 --> 00:24:58.879
Help us, Lord, to keep our eyes on Jesus, the author and finisher of our faith.

00:24:58.879 --> 00:25:02.459
We thank you for the prayer time that we can have on Wednesday evenings.

00:25:02.459 --> 00:25:08.619
And I pray, God, that you would bless and work through the corporate prayer time, Lord,

00:25:08.619 --> 00:25:12.639
that we know, we believe tonight that you hear and you answer prayer.

00:25:12.639 --> 00:25:15.919
And we're so grateful for that biblical truth.

00:25:15.919 --> 00:25:20.119
And I pray that you would just have your will and way throughout the remainder of the service

00:25:20.119 --> 00:25:21.119
tonight.

00:25:21.119 --> 00:25:22.119
For it's in Christ's name we pray.

00:25:22.119 --> 00:25:23.119
Amen.

00:25:23.119 --> 00:25:23.119


